[[Academic]] [[professor]] '''Anastas Todorov Ishirkov''' ({{lang-bg|Анастас Тодоров Иширков}}; 5 April 1868 – 6 April 1937)   was Bulgarian scientist, geographer and ethnographer. He was the founder of geographical science in [[Bulgaria]] and was a member of [[Bulgarian Academy of Sciences]].

==Honours==
[[Ishirkov Crag]] on [[Oscar II Coast]] in [[Graham Land]], [[Antarctica]] is named after Anastas Ishirkov.<ref>[https://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/display_name.cfm?gaz_id=137570 Ishirkov Crag] [https://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/ SCAR Composite Gazetteer of Antarctica]</ref>

