{{Environment-stub}}

The '''geology of Albania''' is a term that embodies the [[Historical geology|geological history]] of [[Albania]]. The Albanides represent the main [[geological]] structures on the territory of the country.<ref>{{cite web |title=GEOPHYSICAL OUTLOOK ON STRUCTURE OF THE ALBANIDES |url=http://itc.upt.al/~nfra/papers/geosciences/Albanides.pdf |website=itc.upt.al |location=Tirana |pages=1-46 |language=English |format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=GEOLOGICAL OVERVIEW |url=http://www.akbn.gov.al/images/pdf/hidrokarburet/Geological-Overview.pdf |website=akbn.gov.al |pages=1-12 |language=English |format=PDF}}</ref> They belong to the [[Alpide belt]] and stretches between the [[Dinarides]] in north and the Hellenides in south within the [[Mediterranean]] belt.  

