'''''These Small Glories''''' was a collection of short stories by Australian author [[Jon Cleary]] which was published in 1946. They were set during [[World War Two]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article206109928 |title=Three New Novels |newspaper=[[The Age]] |issue=28,449 |location=Victoria, Australia |date=29 June 1946 |accessdate=6 August 2017 |page=28 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article140613541 |title="Small Glories" of Middle East |newspaper=[[Newcastle Morning Herald And Miners' Advocate]] |issue=21,752 |location=New South Wales, Australia |date=22 June 1946 |accessdate=6 August 2017 |page=5 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article35705628 |title=Latest Fiction |newspaper=[[The Advertiser (Adelaide)]] |volume=89, |issue=27391 |location=South Australia |date=20 July 1946 |accessdate=6 August 2017 |page=4 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article18008509 |title=CLEARY HEARD NEWS IN LONDON |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |issue=34,014 |location=New South Wales, Australia |date=28 December 1946 |accessdate=6 August 2017 |page=7 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
